===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*bʰeh₂-|id=shine}}
From {{inh|en|enm|epiphanie}}, from {{der|en|fro|epyphanie}}, from {{der|en|LL.|epiphania}}, from {{der|en|grc|ἐπιφάνεια||manifestation, striking appearance}}, from {{m|grc|ἐπιφαίνω||I appear, display}}, from {{m|grc|ἐπί||upon}} + {{m|grc|φαίνω||I shine, appear}}. English [[Epiphany]] (of [[Christ]]) since the 14th century, generic use since the 17th century.

